# Frontend build-time config (Vite inlines VITE_* at `npm run build` /
# `npm run dev`). Copy to web/.env and fill in from your Firebase project's
# web app config (Firebase console → Project settings → Your apps → SDK
# setup and configuration).
#
# These values are PUBLIC client identifiers — Firebase's apiKey is safe to
# expose; security comes from Firebase Auth rules + backend ID-token
# verification, not from hiding these. Still, web/.env is gitignored so each
# deployment supplies its own.
#
# The backend separately needs QPEDIA_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID (= projectId
# below) to verify the ID tokens — set that in the top-level .env.

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project
# Optional — silences an SDK warning; required only if you add Analytics:
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# Optional — enables the "Continue with company SSO" button on /login when
# you've registered an enterprise OIDC provider in the Firebase console:
# VITE_FIREBASE_SSO_PROVIDER_ID=oidc.acme
